finding out what plants really

00:33:13.490 --> 00:33:14.090
need, I guess.

00:33:14.090 --> 00:33:18.320
So identifying what the
plant that you choose--

00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:20.120
what the needs are,
what the soil needs

00:33:20.120 --> 00:33:22.280
are, what the
moisture levels are,

00:33:22.280 --> 00:33:23.780
making sure there's
enough drainage,

00:33:23.780 --> 00:33:26.820
making sure that
it doesn't dry out.

00:33:26.820 --> 00:33:30.930
So if you do have, say, a
pot, you can control that.

00:33:30.930 --> 00:33:31.650
So that's easy.

00:33:31.650 --> 00:33:33.110
You just need to
inform yourself.

00:33:33.110 --> 00:33:37.394
So use Google and find out
exactly what the plant needs.

00:33:37.394 --> 00:33:38.810
I actually use it
on a daily basis

00:33:38.810 --> 00:33:43.220
for all sorts of stuff from
cooking to god knows what.

00:33:43.220 --> 00:33:46.160
But yeah, to inform yourself
of what that plant needs.

00:33:46.160 --> 00:33:48.770
Or to go, right, I
don't have huge amounts

00:33:48.770 --> 00:33:50.870
of rainfall in that
particular area in the garden

00:33:50.870 --> 00:33:51.890
where I have the pots.

00:33:51.890 --> 00:33:55.265
And to go, right, I'm going to
use drought-friendly plants,

00:33:55.265 --> 00:33:57.140
and then find out what
you could plant there.

00:33:57.140 --> 00:34:01.130
And then create a scheme
around that-- so a dry desert

00:34:01.130 --> 00:34:03.590
feel space with grasses
or something like that.

