00:34:15.949 --> 00:34:18.949
If a community-- and I just
say a group of people who live

00:34:18.949 --> 00:34:20.360
in a housing estate--

00:34:20.360 --> 00:34:27.500
decided to create a small
community garden or allotment,

00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:30.170
would you have any
advice on what they could

00:34:30.170 --> 00:34:33.500
do to make that a success?

00:34:33.500 --> 00:34:35.790
LEONIE CORNELIUS: Oh, planning.

00:34:35.790 --> 00:34:36.290
Planning.

00:34:36.290 --> 00:34:37.969
Definitely a huge thing.

00:34:37.969 --> 00:34:40.370
Make sure that you know
exactly what you're doing

00:34:40.370 --> 00:34:42.270
and look at who's
going to be using it.

00:34:42.270 --> 00:34:43.909
So going back to the
user, is it going

00:34:43.909 --> 00:34:46.699
to be the younger
people in the community?

00:34:46.699 --> 00:34:48.689
Will they be involved?

00:34:48.689 --> 00:34:49.980
Is it going to be older people?

00:34:49.980 --> 00:34:51.830
So you might raise beds.

00:34:51.830 --> 00:34:55.130
So finding out the user is
probably the main thing,

00:34:55.130 --> 00:34:59.750
identifying who will be using
it, and then making it fun,

00:34:59.750 --> 00:35:01.620
making sure that the
kids get involved,

00:35:01.620 --> 00:35:03.500
and everybody wants to be there.

00:35:03.500 --> 00:35:07.100
So maybe have some sort of
a social space or something

00:35:07.100 --> 00:35:09.890
in it, like a small gazebo
or a little polytunnel,

00:35:09.890 --> 00:35:11.480
where everyone can hang out.

00:35:11.480 --> 00:35:13.021
Because then you'll
want to be there,

00:35:13.021 --> 00:35:14.654
and you'll want to put work in.

