00:35:21.350 --> 00:35:23.840
AUDIENCE: Yeah, my
first question to ask--

00:35:23.840 --> 00:35:25.950
you probably get asked
this one all the time.

00:35:25.950 --> 00:35:27.195
Is that on?

00:35:27.195 --> 00:35:28.820
LEONIE CORNELIUS: I
can hear you, yeah.

00:35:28.820 --> 00:35:29.990
AUDIENCE: Great.

00:35:29.990 --> 00:35:32.150
What's your take
on synthetic grass?

00:35:32.150 --> 00:35:34.820
Because it's sort of when you're
doing a lot of other stuff,

00:35:34.820 --> 00:35:38.672
it seems like an easy option,
but is it the right option?

00:35:38.672 --> 00:35:40.880
LEONIE CORNELIUS: It's funny,
because a lot of garden

00:35:40.880 --> 00:35:42.860
designers, we had a big
discussion about this

00:35:42.860 --> 00:35:44.060
during Super Garden.

00:35:44.060 --> 00:35:46.640
And 90% of the people that we
were talking to at the time

00:35:46.640 --> 00:35:47.880
were like, oh, it's horrible.

00:35:47.880 --> 00:35:48.470
It's horrible.

00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:50.630
But there's an
absolute place for it.

00:35:50.630 --> 00:35:53.480
Like Today FM have it
on their roof garden,

00:35:53.480 --> 00:35:54.980
and they were ashamed of it.

00:35:54.980 --> 00:35:57.438
And I was like, no, but why
would you put real grass there?

00:35:57.438 --> 00:35:58.820
It would be head-wrecking.

00:35:58.820 --> 00:36:01.190
So I think it depends
on your needs,

00:36:01.190 --> 00:36:03.110
on your needs, on
what you need it for.

00:36:03.110 --> 00:36:07.460
And if you think it'll make
your life easier and better,

00:36:07.460 --> 00:36:09.536
and you can work it into
the design in such a way

00:36:09.536 --> 00:36:11.035
that it looks good,
then absolutely.

00:36:11.035 --> 00:36:12.230
Why not?

00:36:12.230 --> 00:36:15.380
I couldn't be a snob about it.

00:36:15.380 --> 00:36:19.022
I think a lot of people do, and
they almost do it to pretend.

00:36:19.022 --> 00:36:21.302
KAROLINE O'SULLIVAN: Great.

00:36:21.302 --> 00:36:23.890
Got one in the second row here.

