00:36:52.129 --> 00:36:53.920
LEONIE CORNELIUS: You
can come work for me.

00:36:53.920 --> 00:36:55.060
AUDIENCE: Yes.

00:36:55.060 --> 00:36:56.830
Hire me.

00:36:56.830 --> 00:36:57.530
What can we do?

00:36:57.530 --> 00:36:59.080
Like most of us,
we can't probably

00:36:59.080 --> 00:37:03.430
afford at this stage to garden
in Dublin, let alone anything

00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:05.290
in Dublin.

00:37:05.290 --> 00:37:07.870
What can we do to create a
nice space on our balconies,

00:37:07.870 --> 00:37:10.220
or if we don't even have
a balcony, maybe inside,

00:37:10.220 --> 00:37:13.900
like a small oasis
to relax and enjoy

00:37:13.900 --> 00:37:15.652
what we saw on the slides?

00:37:15.652 --> 00:37:17.110
LEONIE CORNELIUS:
Well, first thing

00:37:17.110 --> 00:37:18.760
is I'm concerned with
that quite a lot,

00:37:18.760 --> 00:37:21.700
because I hate
the idea of design

00:37:21.700 --> 00:37:25.540
being exclusive and the
idea that only those that

00:37:25.540 --> 00:37:28.447
have like 100,000 euro to spend
on the design could afford it.

00:37:28.447 --> 00:37:30.030
And the first garden
I did-- actually,

00:37:30.030 --> 00:37:32.210
I don't think there's any
pictures of it in this--

00:37:32.210 --> 00:37:35.650
a bloom was made with
old scaffolding planks.

00:37:35.650 --> 00:37:39.910
And so if you want to
create something really

00:37:39.910 --> 00:37:42.760
special without putting huge
amounts of money into it,

00:37:42.760 --> 00:37:46.180
you have to kind of rethink
the materials you're using.

00:37:46.180 --> 00:37:47.920
You have to rethink
the amount of time

00:37:47.920 --> 00:37:48.920
you want to put into it.

00:37:48.920 --> 00:37:50.230
So those scaffolding planks--

00:37:50.230 --> 00:37:52.880
they looked absolutely stunning
when we were done with them.

00:37:52.880 --> 00:37:54.760
But we sanded and
sanded and sanded

00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:57.640
and sanded to get them
to look really well,

00:37:57.640 --> 00:38:00.130
and then stained them
again and again and again.

00:38:00.130 --> 00:38:02.230
So reimagining old
materials is great,

00:38:02.230 --> 00:38:03.730
but then everybody's
kind of started

00:38:03.730 --> 00:38:04.960
catching on to that, too.

00:38:04.960 --> 00:38:07.480
So scaffolding planks
are hard to get.

00:38:07.480 --> 00:38:08.645
What do you call them?

00:38:08.645 --> 00:38:09.145
Pallets.

00:38:11.720 --> 00:38:13.890
But be creative.

00:38:13.890 --> 00:38:16.780
Get hands-on yourself,
and it doesn't need

00:38:16.780 --> 00:38:18.910
to cost a huge amount of money.

00:38:18.910 --> 00:38:21.160
It's hard to be specific,
because I don't know exactly

00:38:21.160 --> 00:38:22.420
what you're talking about.

00:38:22.420 --> 00:38:25.870
But say, instead of--
if you wanted something

00:38:25.870 --> 00:38:29.440
on a windowsill inside,
instead of just getting

00:38:29.440 --> 00:38:31.840
a plastic window box,
create something,

00:38:31.840 --> 00:38:33.940
even if it's made
with driftwood or made

00:38:33.940 --> 00:38:39.610
with timber that you stain up
to suit the color scheme inside.

00:38:39.610 --> 00:38:43.240
Or go to Pinterest and
research certain things.

00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:46.150
And there's so
many ideas you can

00:38:46.150 --> 00:38:49.360
kind of bring in to the home by
just getting creative yourself.

00:38:49.360 --> 00:38:51.552
I know that's a
really bad answer.

00:38:51.552 --> 00:38:53.260
KAROLINE O'SULLIVAN:
So it's about making

00:38:53.260 --> 00:38:53.910
it a for-real project.

00:38:53.910 --> 00:38:55.420
LEONIE CORNELIUS:
Creativity, yes.

00:38:55.420 --> 00:38:56.020
Yes.

00:38:56.020 --> 00:38:57.770
KAROLINE O'SULLIVAN:
Not just a quick fix,

00:38:57.770 --> 00:38:59.730
which is what I kind of tend
to do when buying a new plant.

00:38:59.730 --> 00:39:00.460
LEONIE CORNELIUS:
But in that way

00:39:00.460 --> 00:39:02.620
you can work design
principles into it,

00:39:02.620 --> 00:39:04.660
and then you'll create
something beautiful, as

00:39:04.660 --> 00:39:06.679
opposed to just
placing something

00:39:06.679 --> 00:39:09.220
that somebody else mightn't have
put a huge amount of thought

00:39:09.220 --> 00:39:09.720
into.

00:39:09.720 --> 00:39:13.630
So it's the thought process, and
then making it personal to you.

00:39:13.630 --> 00:39:17.200
Because if you make it yourself
or have it made, even if it is,

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:20.590
like, say, a gate,
a rusted steel gate,

00:39:20.590 --> 00:39:23.050
it might be old materials,
but you thought it up.

00:39:23.050 --> 00:39:25.671
So you know it's going
to be perfect for you.

00:39:25.671 --> 00:39:27.004
KAROLINE O'SULLIVAN: OK, lovely.

