00:39:45.780 --> 00:39:47.530
Myself and my wife
were talking about what

00:39:47.530 --> 00:39:48.714
we do from the start.

00:39:48.714 --> 00:39:51.130
So, for example, obviously,
we'd be busy inside the house.

00:39:51.130 --> 00:39:53.380
But do you have
any advice in terms

00:39:53.380 --> 00:39:56.470
of if we wanted to put down,
let's say, trees first,

00:39:56.470 --> 00:39:58.420
we start from big and
work our way down?

00:39:58.420 --> 00:40:00.610
Or do we start with
little potted plants

00:40:00.610 --> 00:40:01.662
and work our way up?

00:40:01.662 --> 00:40:03.370
Have you kind of come
across that before?

00:40:03.370 --> 00:40:03.970
Where would you start?

00:40:03.970 --> 00:40:05.170
LEONIE CORNELIUS: Oh, loads.

00:40:05.170 --> 00:40:08.020
And the main thing, I think,
is before you start planting,

00:40:08.020 --> 00:40:11.009
before you start doing
anything is dreaming that,

00:40:11.009 --> 00:40:13.300
that kind of figuring out
what you want from the garden

00:40:13.300 --> 00:40:16.150
before you start placing
things, and even before you

00:40:16.150 --> 00:40:19.820
start going into the privacy
and all of those kind of things.

00:40:19.820 --> 00:40:22.330
So making sure that your
dream for the house, which

00:40:22.330 --> 00:40:24.100
you probably already
have, and you

00:40:24.100 --> 00:40:26.830
have materials and
features in there

00:40:26.830 --> 00:40:29.130
that you want to pick up on
and the style of the house.

00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:30.550
Try and bleed that out.

00:40:30.550 --> 00:40:32.902
So pick up on colors,
materials on the floor.

00:40:32.902 --> 00:40:35.110
Like if you have, say,
concrete floors, bleed it out.

00:40:35.110 --> 00:40:38.380
Or if there's tiles or
timber, try and continue that,

00:40:38.380 --> 00:40:40.990
because then it will become an
extension of your living space.

00:40:40.990 --> 00:40:44.800
But making sure you identify
what kind of feel you want,

00:40:44.800 --> 00:40:48.070
what kind of style
you want, and then

00:40:48.070 --> 00:40:50.410
bleeding that in
through the whole space

00:40:50.410 --> 00:40:51.430
and connecting them.

00:40:51.430 --> 00:40:54.160
And then you can always
start by planting a few trees

00:40:54.160 --> 00:40:55.840
if you wanted to now.

00:40:55.840 --> 00:40:57.800
And then work with
the rest around that.

00:40:57.800 --> 00:40:59.869
But just make sure
that you don't end up

00:40:59.869 --> 00:41:01.910
putting them somewhere
where you don't want them.

00:41:01.910 --> 00:41:03.700
So making sure you
follow the process

00:41:03.700 --> 00:41:07.540
in your head a little bit
of, where do I need privacy?

00:41:07.540 --> 00:41:10.690
Where do I need windscreen?

00:41:10.690 --> 00:41:13.570
So do analyze the site
a bit before you look

00:41:13.570 --> 00:41:15.260
at trees or that sort of thing.

