00:43:04.720 --> 00:43:05.930
AUDIENCE: My question
kind of comes back

00:43:05.930 --> 00:43:07.230
to what we discussed earlier.

00:43:07.230 --> 00:43:10.180
It's like around
style, about style.

00:43:10.180 --> 00:43:13.190
Is there like an Irish
style that you've

00:43:13.190 --> 00:43:16.040
seen over the years, or
how has that developed?

00:43:16.040 --> 00:43:19.160
Or is there something that
makes Irish gardens stand out

00:43:19.160 --> 00:43:22.532
from other, let's
say, European gardens?

00:43:22.532 --> 00:43:23.990
LEONIE CORNELIUS:
It's interesting,

00:43:23.990 --> 00:43:26.810
because for a long
time, Irish design

00:43:26.810 --> 00:43:29.990
would have been influenced
hugely by the likes of Chelsea,

00:43:29.990 --> 00:43:35.990
the RHS shows, Tatton Park, and
all of the big shows, garden

00:43:35.990 --> 00:43:39.260
shows, show garden
shows in the UK.

00:43:39.260 --> 00:43:43.750
I think since Bloom was
launched, which is what?

00:43:43.750 --> 00:43:45.230
11 years ago now.

00:43:45.230 --> 00:43:48.330
I think that kind of gave
Irish designers a platform

00:43:48.330 --> 00:43:50.690
here to showcase.

00:43:50.690 --> 00:43:53.120
So I think there's been
a huge shift in that.

00:43:53.120 --> 00:43:58.130
And I think an Irish planting
style and feel has developed,

00:43:58.130 --> 00:44:02.270
which is a little bit more
relaxed and natural than, say,

00:44:02.270 --> 00:44:03.470
its English counterpart.

00:44:03.470 --> 00:44:07.550
Having said that, trends
kind of cross over and back,

00:44:07.550 --> 00:44:11.070
and you've got trends coming
from the south of France,

00:44:11.070 --> 00:44:14.780
and there's like an overall
trend of naturalistic planting

00:44:14.780 --> 00:44:17.600
and sustainability,
and allowing gardens

00:44:17.600 --> 00:44:20.390
to just be the way
they want to be,

00:44:20.390 --> 00:44:23.120
which, actually, last year,
came back a little bit

00:44:23.120 --> 00:44:25.490
to be more structured, again.

00:44:25.490 --> 00:44:27.630
So there are trends that
go across all of them.

00:44:27.630 --> 00:44:29.240
But I do think
Irish designers have

00:44:29.240 --> 00:44:31.810
developed their own styles.

00:44:31.810 --> 00:44:34.280
And I think this year at Bloom,
it was interesting to see.

00:44:34.280 --> 00:44:36.020
There was a lot of
interest at Chelsea,

00:44:36.020 --> 00:44:38.840
and the Chelsea designers were
tweeting a lot about designers

00:44:38.840 --> 00:44:40.460
here and about what
gardens they liked

00:44:40.460 --> 00:44:43.610
and stuff, which was
amazing to have that coming

00:44:43.610 --> 00:44:45.134
back to Ireland.

00:44:45.134 --> 00:44:46.550
KAROLINE O'SULLIVAN:
That's great.

